<TITLE> Lifting ban will allow parties to sit with EC: Bhuiyan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com) Breakaway BNP faction chief Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan Sunday said the latest government decision would enable political parties to thrash out electoral reforms with the Election Commission. "I welcome the decision of lifting ban on indoor politics by the government. This would allow the political parties to meet among themselves and discuss with the Election Commission," Bhuiyan told bdnews24.com. He hoped the Election Commission would now be able to hold the national polls in line with its roadmap. He also called upon the political parties to extend cooperation to the government in its efforts to hold the polls. bdnew
